"Freestanding ambulatory care facility" means:
An ambulatory surgical facility;
A freestanding endoscopy facility;
A freestanding facility utilizing major medical equipment;
A kidney dialysis center; or
A freestanding birthing center.

"Major medical equipment" means:
Cardiac catheterization equipment;
A computer tomography (CT) scanner;
A lithotripter;
Radiation therapy equipment, including a linear accelerator; or
A magnetic resonance imager (MRI).
